This paper deals with medical image analysis, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of crowd annotations also suggests a potential focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of statistical measures such as standard deviations, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the prediction of whether a skin lesion is a melanoma or not could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves analyzing visual characteristics of an image.
